<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08120</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING THE MANUFACTURE, SALE, DISTRIBUTION AND USE OF RINSE-OFF COSMETICS AND CLOTHING CONTAINING MICROPLASTICS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Prohibits the manufacture, sale, importation or distribution of rinse-off cosmetics such as facial scrubs, body wash, toothpaste, and similar products containing  plastic microbeads; and garments, clothing, apparel that contain microfiber. Penalizes the violation of this Act with a fine of P500,000.00 pesos to P1.5 million pesos, revocation of Business Permit and imprisonment ranging from 3 to 6 years.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Microplastic Ban Act of 2018.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BATOCABE, RODEL M., GARBIN, ALFREDO JR. A., CO, CHRISTOPHER S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-16</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Nieto (000 2018-09-17)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECOLOGY ON 2018-08-28</td></tr></table>